anyone has been talking about.

935
01:01:01,492 --> 01:01:03,052
Why have you come here?

936
01:01:03,732 --> 01:01:07,932
I'm Miguel.
Your great-great-grandson.

937
01:01:09,252 --> 01:01:12,092
I... have a great-great-grandson?

938
01:01:12,132 --> 01:01:13,492
I need your blessing

939
01:01:13,572 --> 01:01:15,612
so I can go back home
and be a musician.

940
01:01:15,772 --> 01:01:17,492
Just like you.

941
01:01:17,572 --> 01:01:20,692
The rest of our family,
they wouldn't listen.

942
01:01:21,372 --> 01:01:24,212
But I hoped you would.

943
01:01:26,012 --> 01:01:30,572
My boy, with a talent like yours,
how could I not listen?

944
01:01:32,052 --> 01:01:33,812
Aww!

945
01:01:33,892 --> 01:01:36,252
I have a great-great-grandson!

946
01:01:43,092 --> 01:01:46,332
-Look! It's Frida!
-Yes, it is I. Frida Kahlo.

947
01:01:46,412 --> 01:01:49,052
-It is an honor, <i>Señora.</i>
<i>-Gracias.</i>

948
01:01:53,492 --> 01:01:55,332
Hey, Negrete! Infante!

949
01:01:55,412 --> 01:01:57,052
Have you met my great-great-grandson?

950
01:01:57,732 --> 01:01:59,452
My great-great-grandson.

951
01:01:59,692 --> 01:02:01,892
He's alive! And a musician to boot!

952
01:02:02,052 --> 01:02:03,932
Dimple. No dimple.
Dimple. No dimple.

953
01:02:04,092 --> 01:02:05,132
No dimple!

954
01:02:05,252 --> 01:02:06,292
<i>To our friendship.</i>

955
01:02:06,932 --> 01:02:10,252
I would move Heaven and Earth
for you, <i>mi amigo. Salud!</i>

956
01:02:11,892 --> 01:02:12,932
Poison!

957
01:02:13,652 --> 01:02:15,652
You know, I did all my own stunts.

958
01:02:15,852 --> 01:02:19,532
<i>♪ Though I have to say goodbye</i>
<i>Remember me... ♪</i>

959
01:02:21,492 --> 01:02:24,012
All of this came
from my amazing fans

960
01:02:24,092 --> 01:02:25,492
in the Land of the Living.

961
01:02:26,572 --> 01:02:29,652
They leave me more offerings
than I know what to do with!

962
01:02:30,692 --> 01:02:33,972
Hey, what's wrong? Is it too much?
You look overwhelmed.

963
01:02:34,132 --> 01:02:37,332
-No! It's all great!
-But?

964
01:02:37,532 --> 01:02:39,532
It's just--

965
01:02:39,612 --> 01:02:41,732
I have been looking up to you
my whole life.

966
01:02:41,932 --> 01:02:44,932
You're the guy who actually did it!

967
01:02:46,292 --> 01:02:49,172
But did you ever regret it?

968
01:02:49,252 --> 01:02:52,052
Choosing music over everything else?

969
01:02:52,972 --> 01:02:54,572
It was hard.

970
01:02:54,652 --> 01:02:58,332
Saying goodbye to my hometown.
Heading off on my own...

971
01:02:59,652 --> 01:03:00,812
Leaving your family?

972
01:03:01,692 --> 01:03:05,932
<i>Sí.</i> But I could not have
done it differently.

973
01:03:06,572 --> 01:03:09,412
One cannot deny
who one is meant to be.

974
01:03:10,092 --> 01:03:14,172
And you, my great-great-grandson,
are meant to be a musician!

975
01:03:16,852 --> 01:03:19,372
You and I, we are artists, Miguel.

976
01:03:19,492 --> 01:03:21,292
We cannot belong to one family.

977
01:03:21,492 --> 01:03:23,732
The world is our family.

978
01:03:25,332 --> 01:03:27,052
Ooh! Ooh! The fireworks have begun!

979
01:03:38,732 --> 01:03:42,212
Soon the party will move across town
for my Sunrise Spectacular.

980
01:03:43,052 --> 01:03:45,932
Miguel,
you must come to the show!

981
01:03:46,012 --> 01:03:47,932
You will be my guest of honor!

982
01:03:48,092 --> 01:03:50,172
-You mean it?
-Of course, my boy.

983
01:03:52,172 --> 01:03:54,332
I can't.

984
01:03:54,412 --> 01:03:56,852
I have to get home before sunrise.

985
01:03:57,012 --> 01:03:59,012
Oh! I really do need to get you home.

986
01:04:03,412 --> 01:04:06,172
It has been an honor.

987
01:04:06,252 --> 01:04:07,972
I am sorry to see you go, Miguel.

988
01:04:08,732 --> 01:04:10,052
I hope you die very soon.

989
01:04:12,132 --> 01:04:14,332
You know what I mean.

990
01:04:16,852 --> 01:04:19,572
Miguel, I give you my bless--

991
01:04:19,652 --> 01:04:21,052
We had a deal, <i>chamaco.</i>

992
01:04:21,692 --> 01:04:24,452
Who are you?
What is the meaning of this?

993
01:04:25,292 --> 01:04:27,652
Oh, Frida! I thought you couldn't make it.

994
01:04:28,052 --> 01:04:30,212
You said you'd take back my photo.

995
01:04:30,292 --> 01:04:31,572
You promised, Miguel.

996
01:04:31,732 --> 01:04:33,652
You know this, uh, man?

997
01:04:33,852 --> 01:04:36,852
Uh, I just met him tonight.
He told me he knew you.

998
01:04:37,772 --> 01:04:39,332
Héctor?

999
01:04:39,852 --> 01:04:42,772
Please, Miguel. Put my photo up.

1000
01:04:44,932 --> 01:04:48,932
My friend, you're being forgotten.

1001
01:04:49,092 --> 01:04:50,732
-And whose fault is that?
-Héctor, please...

1002
01:04:50,892 --> 01:04:53,612
Those were my songs you took.
My songs that made you famous.

1003
01:04:53,772 --> 01:04:54,812
What?

1004
01:04:55,172 --> 01:04:58,052
If I'm being forgotten, it's because
you never told anyone that I wrote them!

1005
01:04:58,172 --> 01:05:01,252
That's crazy! De la Cruz wrote
all his own songs.

1006
01:05:01,412 --> 01:05:03,132
You want to tell him or should I?

1007
01:05:03,372 --> 01:05:05,732
Héctor, I never meant to take credit.

1008
01:05:05,812 --> 01:05:09,092
We made a great team, but you died...

1009
01:05:09,252 --> 01:05:11,252
and I only sang your songs

1010
01:05:11,332 --> 01:05:14,172
because I wanted to keep
a part of you alive.

1011
01:05:14,332 --> 01:05:15,812
Oh, how generous!

1012
01:05:15,972 --> 01:05:18,092
You really did play together.

1013
01:05:18,252 --> 01:05:20,652
I don't want to fight about it.

1014
01:05:20,732 --> 01:05:22,292
I just want you to make it right.

1015
01:05:22,452 --> 01:05:26,132
Miguel can put my photo up,
and I can cross over the bridge.

1016
01:05:27,332 --> 01:05:28,932
I can see my girl.

1017
01:05:29,012 --> 01:05:31,972
Ernesto, remember the night I left?

1018
01:05:32,132 --> 01:05:33,652
That was a long time ago.

1019
01:05:33,812 --> 01:05:37,052
We drank together and you told me
you would move Heaven and Earth...

1020
01:05:37,092 --> 01:05:41,132
for your <i>amigo.</i>
Well, I'm asking you to now.

1021
01:05:41,292 --> 01:05:43,532
Heaven and Earth?
Like in the movie?

1022
01:05:43,692 --> 01:05:46,172
-What?
-That's Don Hidalgo's toast.

1023
01:05:46,332 --> 01:05:48,772
In the de la Cruz movie,
<i>El Camino a Casa.</i>

1024
01:05:48,972 --> 01:05:50,172
I'm talking about my real life, Miguel.

1025
01:05:50,252 --> 01:05:52,852
No! It's in there. Look!

1026
01:05:52,932 --> 01:05:54,452
<i>Never were</i>
<i>truer words spoken.</i>

1027
01:05:54,532 --> 01:05:57,052
<i>This calls for a toast.</i>
<i>To our friendship!</i>

1028
01:05:57,732 --> 01:06:00,132
<i>I would move Heaven and Earth</i>
<i>for you,</i> mi amigo.

1029
01:06:00,292 --> 01:06:02,932
But in the movie,
Don Hidalgo poisons the drink.

1030
01:06:03,492 --> 01:06:06,052
- Salud!
<i>- Poison!</i>

1031
01:06:08,372 --> 01:06:11,932
That night, Ernesto. The night I left...

1032
01:06:12,812 --> 01:06:15,252
<i>We'd been performing</i>
<i>on the road for months.</i>

1033
01:06:15,252 --> 01:06:16,532
<i>I got homesick...</i>

1034
01:06:16,612 --> 01:06:17,932
<i>and I packed up my songs.</i>

1035
01:06:19,052 --> 01:06:20,132
You want to give up now

1036
01:06:20,212 --> 01:06:22,492
when we're this close
to reaching our dream?

1037
01:06:22,652 --> 01:06:24,532
This was your dream. You'll manage.

1038
01:06:24,692 --> 01:06:26,372
I can't do this
without your songs, Héctor.

1039
01:06:26,732 --> 01:06:27,852
I'm going home, Ernesto.

1040
01:06:27,972 --> 01:06:30,252
Hate me if you want,
but my mind is made up.

1041
01:06:33,652 --> 01:06:36,932
Oh, I could never hate you.
If you must go,

1042
01:06:37,012 --> 01:06:39,652
then I'm sending you off with a toast.

1043
01:06:43,652 --> 01:06:44,892
To our friendship.

1044
01:06:45,052 --> 01:06:49,052
I would move Heaven and Earth
for you, <i>mi amigo. Salud!</i>

1045
01:06:53,852 --> 01:06:55,372
<i>You walked me</i>
<i>to the train station.</i>

1046
01:06:55,452 --> 01:06:57,612
<i>But I felt a pain in my stomach.</i>

1047
01:06:58,452 --> 01:07:00,572
<i>I thought it must have been</i>
<i>something I ate.</i>

1048
01:07:00,732 --> 01:07:02,412
Perhaps it was that <i>chorizo,</i> my friend.

1049
01:07:03,172 --> 01:07:05,412
<i>Or something I drank.</i>

1050
01:07:09,092 --> 01:07:10,772
<i>I woke up dead.</i>

1051
01:07:12,652 --> 01:07:14,852
You poisoned me.

1052
01:07:15,012 --> 01:07:18,212
You're confusing movies
with reality, Héctor.

1053
01:07:18,372 --> 01:07:21,652
All this time, I thought
it was just bad luck.

1054
01:07:23,732 --> 01:07:27,812
<i>I never thought that</i>
<i>you might have-- That you...</i>

1055
01:07:31,052 --> 01:07:32,692
-How could you?
-Héctor!

1056
01:07:32,892 --> 01:07:34,172
Security! Security!

1057
01:07:35,092 --> 01:07:38,612
You took everything
away from me! You rat!

1058
01:07:39,972 --> 01:07:42,532
Have him taken care of.
He's not well.

1059
01:07:43,412 --> 01:07:48,052
I just wanted to go back home.
No! No!

1060
01:07:49,372 --> 01:07:52,572
I apologize.
Where were we?

1061
01:07:52,732 --> 01:07:54,852
You were going to give me
your blessing.

1062
01:07:55,052 --> 01:07:57,212
Yes. Uh, <i>sí.</i>

1063
01:08:00,492 --> 01:08:03,652
Miguel, uh, my reputation...

1064
01:08:04,252 --> 01:08:07,812
It is very important to me.

1065
01:08:07,892 --> 01:08:09,852
I would hate to have you think...

1066
01:08:10,012 --> 01:08:13,972
That you murdered Héctor
for his songs?

1067
01:08:15,332 --> 01:08:18,292
You don't think that. Do you?

1068
01:08:18,732 --> 01:08:22,892
I-- No. Everyone
knows you're the good guy.

1069
01:08:29,972 --> 01:08:32,372
<i>Papá</i> Ernesto, my blessing?

1070
01:08:35,012 --> 01:08:39,572
Security? Take care of Miguel.
He'll be extending his stay.

1071
01:08:39,732 --> 01:08:42,772
What? But I'm your family!

1072
01:08:42,932 --> 01:08:44,172
And Héctor was my best friend.

1073
01:08:45,332 --> 01:08:48,172
Success doesn't come for free, Miguel.

1074
01:08:48,852 --> 01:08:51,012
You have to be willing to do
whatever it takes

1075
01:08:51,092 --> 01:08:54,012
to seize your moment.

1076
01:08:54,452 --> 01:08:55,772
I know you understand.

1077
01:08:56,372 --> 01:08:58,292
No! No!

1078
01:09:00,932 --> 01:09:03,292
Let go! No!

1079
01:09:25,892 --> 01:09:30,212
Help!
Can anyone hear me?

1080
01:09:30,292 --> 01:09:32,452
I want to go home.

1081
01:09:51,292 --> 01:09:52,652
- Héctor?
- Kid?

1082
01:09:53,132 --> 01:09:56,052
Oh, Héctor! You were right.

1083
01:09:56,132 --> 01:09:58,252
I should have gone back to my family.

1084
01:09:58,612 --> 01:10:01,092
They told me not to be like de la Cruz,

1085
01:10:01,172 --> 01:10:02,772
but I didn't listen.

1086
01:10:02,932 --> 01:10:05,772
I told them I didn't care
if they remembered me.

1087
01:10:05,932 --> 01:10:08,732
I didn't care if I was
on their stupid <i>ofrenda.</i>

1088
01:10:09,372 --> 01:10:12,092
Hey, <i>chamaco.</i>
It's okay. It's okay.

1089
01:10:12,252 --> 01:10:14,692
I told them I didn't care.

1090
01:10:18,692 --> 01:10:21,532
Héctor! Héctor?

1091
01:10:22,532 --> 01:10:25,132
She's forgetting me.

1092
01:10:25,812 --> 01:10:28,732
-Who?
-My daughter.

1093
01:10:31,412 --> 01:10:35,332
She's the reason you wanted
to cross the bridge.

1094
01:10:35,972 --> 01:10:39,292
I just wanted to see her again.

1095
01:10:39,372 --> 01:10:41,492
I never should have left Santa Cecilia.

1096
01:10:43,252 --> 01:10:45,092
I wish I could apologize.

1097
01:10:45,252 --> 01:10:48,292
I wish I could tell her
that her <i>papá</i> was trying to come home.

1098
01:10:49,252 --> 01:10:51,372
That he loved her so much.

1099
01:10:54,172 --> 01:10:55,652
My Coco...

1100
01:10:57,932 --> 01:10:59,332
Coco?

1101
01:11:15,572 --> 01:11:17,612
Where did you get this?

1102
01:11:18,932 --> 01:11:22,332
That's my <i>Mamá</i> Coco.
That's my <i>Mamá</i> Imelda.

1103
01:11:23,652 --> 01:11:26,412
Is that you?

1104
01:11:30,332 --> 01:11:33,572
- We're...
- Family?

1105
01:11:46,172 --> 01:11:48,732
I always hoped
I'd see her again.

1106
01:11:48,812 --> 01:11:50,652
That she'd miss me.

1107
01:11:51,332 --> 01:11:55,012
Maybe put up my photo.
But it never happened.

1108
01:11:56,372 --> 01:11:57,732
You know the worst part?

1109
01:11:58,572 --> 01:12:00,732
Even if I never got to see
Coco in the living world...

1110
01:12:01,092 --> 01:12:04,292
I thought at least
one day I'd see her here.

1111
01:12:04,372 --> 01:12:05,892
Give her the biggest hug.

1112
01:12:08,252 --> 01:12:10,852
But she's the last person
who remembers me.

1113
01:12:12,012 --> 01:12:14,172
The moment she's gone
from the living world...

1114
01:12:14,332 --> 01:12:18,132
You disappear... from this one.

1115
01:12:18,212 --> 01:12:19,932
You'll never get to see her.

1116
01:12:20,092 --> 01:12:21,692
Ever again.

1117
01:12:25,052 --> 01:12:27,572
You know, I wrote her a song once.

1118
01:12:28,212 --> 01:12:31,612
We used to sing it every night
at the same time.

1119
01:12:32,292 --> 01:12:34,532
No matter how far apart we were.

1120
01:12:35,852 --> 01:12:38,412
What I wouldn't give to sing it to her

1121
01:12:38,492 --> 01:12:41,252
one... last... time.

1122
01:12:43,452 --> 01:12:46,652
<i>♪ Remember me</i>

1123
01:12:47,332 --> 01:12:51,732
<i>♪ Though I have to say goodbye</i>
<i>Remember me</i>

1124
01:12:53,052 --> 01:12:55,972
<i>♪ Don't let it make you cry</i>

1125
01:12:56,092 --> 01:13:01,292
<i>♪ For even if I'm far away</i>
<i>I hold you in my heart</i>

1126
01:13:01,972 --> 01:13:07,172
<i>♪ I sing a secret song to you</i>
<i>Each night we are apart</i>

1127
01:13:08,812 --> 01:13:11,172
<i>♪ Remember me</i>

1128
01:13:11,252 --> 01:13:12,212
<i>Papá!</i>

1129
01:13:12,412 --> 01:13:16,452
<i>♪ Though I have to travel far</i>
<i>Remember me</i>

1130
01:13:17,692 --> 01:13:20,892
<i>♪ Each time you hear a sad guitar</i>

1131
01:13:21,572 --> 01:13:27,332
<i>♪ Know that I'm with you</i>
<i>The only way that I can be</i>

1132
01:13:29,652 --> 01:13:33,892
<i>♪ Until you're in my arms again</i>

1133
01:13:36,132 --> 01:13:42,452
<i>♪ Remember me ♪</i>

1134
01:13:48,572 --> 01:13:51,852
He stole your guitar.
He stole your songs.

1135
01:13:52,692 --> 01:13:56,332
You should be the one
the world remembers, not de la Cruz!

1136
01:13:56,492 --> 01:13:59,172
I didn't write <i>Remember Me</i>
for the world.

1137
01:13:59,252 --> 01:14:00,692
I wrote it for Coco.

1138
01:14:02,772 --> 01:14:05,412
I'm a pretty sorry excuse
for a great-great-grandpa.

1139
01:14:05,692 --> 01:14:08,852
Are you kidding? A minute ago
I thought I was related to a murderer.

1140
01:14:09,052 --> 01:14:11,252
You're a total upgrade.

1141
01:14:11,372 --> 01:14:13,732
My whole life, there's been something...

1142
01:14:13,932 --> 01:14:15,532
that made me different.

1143
01:14:15,572 --> 01:14:17,532
And I never knew where it came from.

1144
01:14:18,852 --> 01:14:21,332
But now I know. It comes from you.

1145
01:14:22,372 --> 01:14:27,172
I'm proud we're family!
I'm proud to be his family!

1146
01:14:34,212 --> 01:14:36,772
I'm proud to be his family!

1147
01:14:51,892 --> 01:14:53,292
Dante?

1148
01:14:53,812 --> 01:14:55,932
Dante!

1149
01:14:58,932 --> 01:14:59,932
It's Dante!

1150
01:15:11,852 --> 01:15:14,612
-Imelda!
-Héctor.

1151
01:15:15,652 --> 01:15:16,972
You look good.

1152
01:15:28,292 --> 01:15:31,452
Dante! You knew he was my
<i>Papá</i> Héctor the whole time!

1153
01:15:31,612 --> 01:15:33,492
You are a real spirit guide.

1154
01:15:33,652 --> 01:15:36,132
Who's the good spirit guide?
You are!

1155
01:15:47,492 --> 01:15:48,892
Whoa!

1156
01:15:56,212 --> 01:15:57,572
Dante!

1157
01:16:21,052 --> 01:16:22,172
There they are!

1158
01:16:22,332 --> 01:16:26,452
Miguel! Miguelito! Look,
it's Miguel! He's all right.

1159
01:16:28,172 --> 01:16:30,852
<i>Gracias, Dios mío.</i>
<i>Qué bueno.</i>

1160
01:16:45,452 --> 01:16:47,372
<i>Mijo,</i> I was so worried!

1161
01:16:47,412 --> 01:16:49,332
Thank goodness we found you in time.

1162
01:16:50,652 --> 01:16:54,052
And you... How many times
must I turn you away?

1163
01:16:54,092 --> 01:16:55,092
Imelda.

1164
01:16:55,212 --> 01:16:58,532
I want nothing to do with you!
Not in life, not in death!

1165
01:16:58,772 --> 01:17:02,212
I spent decades protecting
my family from your mistakes.

1166
01:17:02,292 --> 01:17:05,772
He spends five minutes with you
and I have to fish him out of a sinkhole!

1167
01:17:05,812 --> 01:17:07,412
I wasn't in there because of Héctor.

1168
01:17:07,572 --> 01:17:10,052
He was in there because of me.

1169
01:17:10,092 --> 01:17:12,052
He was just trying to get me home!

1170
01:17:12,452 --> 01:17:15,692
I didn't want to listen, but he was right.

1171
01:17:16,772 --> 01:17:18,732
Nothing's more important than family.

1172
01:17:20,052 --> 01:17:22,532
I'm ready to accept your blessing.

1173
01:17:23,172 --> 01:17:25,172
And your conditions.

1174
01:17:25,292 --> 01:17:27,252
But first, I need to find de la Cruz.

1175
01:17:27,612 --> 01:17:29,132
To get Héctor's photo.

1176
01:17:29,172 --> 01:17:30,932
-What?
-So he can see Coco again.

1177
01:17:31,132 --> 01:17:32,892
Héctor should be on our <i>ofrenda.</i>

1178
01:17:32,932 --> 01:17:34,052
He's part of our family.

1179
01:17:34,532 --> 01:17:35,692
He left this family!

1180
01:17:35,892 --> 01:17:37,612
He tried to go home to you and Coco.

1181
01:17:37,692 --> 01:17:39,292
But de la Cruz murdered him!

1182
01:17:40,612 --> 01:17:44,532
-It's true, Imelda.
-And so what if it's true?

1183
01:17:44,692 --> 01:17:46,932
You leave me alone
with a child to raise...

1184
01:17:47,092 --> 01:17:49,052
and I'm just supposed to forgive you?

1185
01:17:49,212 --> 01:17:50,292
Imelda, I--

1186
01:17:51,132 --> 01:17:53,212
Héctor!

1187
01:17:54,932 --> 01:17:58,492
I'm running out of time.
It's Coco.

1188
01:17:59,812 --> 01:18:01,332
She's forgetting you.

1189
01:18:02,652 --> 01:18:07,412
You don't have to forgive him.
But we shouldn't forget him.

1190
01:18:10,052 --> 01:18:12,652
I wanted to forget you.

1191
01:18:13,572 --> 01:18:16,332
I wanted Coco to forget you too, but...

1192
01:18:16,492 --> 01:18:19,132
This is my fault. Not yours.

1193
01:18:21,572 --> 01:18:23,372
I'm sorry, Imelda.

1194
01:18:27,652 --> 01:18:31,172
Miguel, if we help you get his photo,

1195
01:18:31,372 --> 01:18:32,812
you will return home?

1196
01:18:32,972 --> 01:18:34,332
No more music?

1197
01:18:35,692 --> 01:18:37,852
Family comes first.

1198
01:18:39,852 --> 01:18:42,972
I can't forgive you.

1199
01:18:45,652 --> 01:18:47,172
But I will help you.

1200
01:18:48,532 --> 01:18:51,092
So, how do we get to de la Cruz?

1201
01:18:52,452 --> 01:18:54,812
I might know a way.

1202
01:19:45,732 --> 01:19:47,852
-Good luck, <i>muchacho.</i>
<i>-Gracias,</i> Frida.

1203
01:19:56,852 --> 01:19:58,612
-Here, let me help you with--
-Don't touch me!

1204
01:19:59,932 --> 01:20:02,092
-Everyone clear on the plan?
-Find Héctor's photo.

1205
01:20:02,252 --> 01:20:03,932
-Give it to Miguel.
-Send Miguel home.

1206
01:20:04,092 --> 01:20:05,772
Got your petals?

1207
01:20:06,932 --> 01:20:08,452
Now, we just have to find de la Cruz.

1208
01:20:08,532 --> 01:20:09,532
Yes?

1209
01:20:10,852 --> 01:20:12,412
Don't I know you?

1210
01:20:13,612 --> 01:20:16,292
That's for murdering the love of my life!

1211
01:20:16,372 --> 01:20:18,292
-Who-- Who the--
-She's talking about me!

1212
01:20:18,372 --> 01:20:19,692
I'm the love of your life?

1213
01:20:19,772 --> 01:20:21,092
I don't know. I'm still angry at you.

1214
01:20:21,452 --> 01:20:22,612
Héctor! How did you--

1215
01:20:22,852 --> 01:20:25,612
And that's for trying
to murder my grandson.

1216
01:20:25,812 --> 01:20:27,492
-Grandson?
-She's talking about me!

1217
01:20:28,052 --> 01:20:31,972
You! Wait.
You're related to Héctor?

1218
01:20:32,132 --> 01:20:33,532
The photo!

1219
01:20:35,652 --> 01:20:36,892
Uh...

1220
01:20:37,132 --> 01:20:38,652
After him!

1221
01:20:41,052 --> 01:20:42,492
Security! <i>Ayúdenme!</i>

1222
01:20:43,252 --> 01:20:46,132
-You said love of your life.
-I don't know what I said.

1223
01:20:46,292 --> 01:20:47,492
That's what I heard.

1224
01:21:00,692 --> 01:21:02,772
Places, <i>Señor.</i>
You're on in thirty seconds.

1225
01:21:09,652 --> 01:21:12,532
<i>Ay!</i> Miguel! I have it!

1226
01:21:21,012 --> 01:21:22,172
Oh!

1227
01:21:28,572 --> 01:21:30,572
Hurry! Come on!

1228
01:21:32,212 --> 01:21:34,012
<i>Ladies and gentlemen...</i>

1229
01:21:34,772 --> 01:21:40,532
<i>the one... the only... Ernesto de la Cruz!</i>

1230
01:21:48,532 --> 01:21:49,692
Get her off the stage.

1231
01:21:58,452 --> 01:22:00,732
Sing! Sing!

1232
01:22:07,172 --> 01:22:11,652
<i>♪ Ay, de mi Llorona</i>

1233
01:22:12,892 --> 01:22:17,612
<i>♪ Llorona de azul celeste</i>

1234
01:22:20,532 --> 01:22:23,972
<i>♪ Ay, de mi Llorona</i>

1235
01:22:25,372 --> 01:22:29,492
<i>♪ Llorona de azul celeste</i>

1236
01:22:32,012 --> 01:22:36,132
<i>♪ Y aunque la vida me cueste,</i>
<i>Llorona</i>

1237
01:22:36,812 --> 01:22:44,212
<i>♪ No dejaré de quererte</i>

1238
01:22:47,532 --> 01:22:50,852
<i>♪ Me subí al pino más alto,</i>
<i>Llorona</i>

1239
01:22:51,012 --> 01:22:53,452
<i>♪ A ver si te divisaba</i>

1240
01:22:53,612 --> 01:22:58,252
<i>♪ Como el pino era tierno,</i>
<i>Llorona</i>

1241
01:22:58,332 --> 01:23:01,292
<i>♪ Al verme llorar, lloraba</i>

1242
01:23:01,452 --> 01:23:07,732
<i>♪ Ay de mí Llorona, Llorona</i>
<i>Llorona de azul celeste</i>

1243
01:23:08,572 --> 01:23:14,932
<i>♪ Ay de mí Llorona, Llorona</i>
<i>Llorona de azul celeste</i>

1244
01:23:15,612 --> 01:23:19,452
<i>♪ Y aunque la vida me cueste,</i>
<i>Llorona</i>

1245
01:23:19,652 --> 01:23:22,692
<i>♪ No dejaré de quererte</i>

1246
01:23:23,052 --> 01:23:24,692
Let go of me!

1247
01:23:24,812 --> 01:23:26,452
<i>♪ Y aunque la vida me cueste,</i>
<i>Llorona</i>

1248
01:23:27,012 --> 01:23:38,212
<i>♪ No dejaré de quererte</i>

1249
01:23:38,932 --> 01:23:41,412
<i>♪ Ay, ay, ay ♪</i>

1250
01:23:50,732 --> 01:23:52,652
I forgot what that felt like.

1251
01:23:52,852 --> 01:23:55,212
You still got it.

1252
01:23:56,372 --> 01:23:58,812
Oh.

1253
01:24:01,572 --> 01:24:04,292
Miguel, I give you my blessing.

1254
01:24:05,932 --> 01:24:09,852
To go home, to put up our photos

1255
01:24:09,932 --> 01:24:11,492
and to never--

1256
01:24:11,652 --> 01:24:13,772
Never play music again.

1257
01:24:15,092 --> 01:24:19,652
To never forget how much
your family loves you.

1258
01:24:22,332 --> 01:24:23,572
You're going home.

1259
01:24:26,692 --> 01:24:28,812
You're not going anywhere.

1260
01:24:30,332 --> 01:24:31,892
Imelda!

1261
01:24:32,292 --> 01:24:33,252
Stay back! Stay back!

1262
01:24:33,332 --> 01:24:37,332
All of you, stay back.
Not one more step.

1263
01:24:39,292 --> 01:24:40,532
Dante!

1264
01:24:42,212 --> 01:24:46,452
Ernesto, stop!
Leave the boy alone.

1265
01:24:46,532 --> 01:24:48,372
I've worked too hard, Héctor.

1266
01:24:48,452 --> 01:24:50,732
Too hard to let him destroy everything.

1267
01:24:50,892 --> 01:24:52,812
He's a living child, Ernesto.

1268
01:24:53,052 --> 01:24:54,372
He's a threat!

1269
01:24:54,492 --> 01:24:56,172
<i>You think I'd let him go back</i>

1270
01:24:56,372 --> 01:24:58,052
<i>to the Land of the Living</i>
<i>with your photo?</i>

1271
01:24:58,292 --> 01:25:01,172
To keep your memory alive? No.

1272
01:25:01,372 --> 01:25:04,012
-You're a coward!
-I am Ernesto de la Cruz.

1273
01:25:04,212 --> 01:25:05,812
The greatest musician of all time!

1274
01:25:06,132 --> 01:25:07,772
Héctor's the real musician.

1275
01:25:08,052 --> 01:25:09,372
<i>You're just the guy who murdered him</i>

1276
01:25:09,532 --> 01:25:10,652
<i>and stole his songs!</i>

1277
01:25:10,732 --> 01:25:12,132
Murdered?

1278
01:25:12,212 --> 01:25:13,772
I am the one who's willing to do

1279
01:25:13,892 --> 01:25:15,492
what it takes to seize my moment.

1280
01:25:16,172 --> 01:25:17,652
Whatever it takes.

1281
01:25:18,692 --> 01:25:21,292
No!

1282
01:25:23,492 --> 01:25:24,732
Miguel!

1283
01:25:25,532 --> 01:25:28,852
Apologies, old friend.
But the show must go on.

1284
01:26:11,172 --> 01:26:13,852
Please, please, <i>mi familia.</i>

1285
01:26:14,012 --> 01:26:15,972
Murderer!

1286
01:26:16,052 --> 01:26:18,452
Orchestra. A-one, a-two, a-one--

1287
01:26:21,092 --> 01:26:24,292
<i>♪ Remember me</i>
<i>Though I have to s-- ♪</i>

1288
01:26:24,332 --> 01:26:25,332
Hey!

1289
01:26:26,772 --> 01:26:27,772
Look!

1290
01:26:48,492 --> 01:26:50,732
Nice kitty.

1291
01:26:53,852 --> 01:26:58,492
Put me down! No, please!
I beg of you! Stop! Stop! No!

1292
01:27:07,052 --> 01:27:08,612
No! No!

1293
01:27:20,532 --> 01:27:21,692
What did I miss?

1294
01:27:21,972 --> 01:27:23,532
Good boy, Dante!

1295
01:27:23,692 --> 01:27:24,692
Miguel!

1296
01:27:26,372 --> 01:27:30,372
Héctor! The photo... I lost it!

1297
01:27:30,812 --> 01:27:33,652
It's okay, <i>mijo.</i> It's o--

1298
01:27:33,732 --> 01:27:36,212
Héctor! Héctor?

1299
01:27:37,492 --> 01:27:38,452
Coco.

1300
01:27:38,652 --> 01:27:40,572
No! We can still find the photo.

1301
01:27:41,172 --> 01:27:42,732
Miguel, it's almost sunrise.

1302
01:27:44,052 --> 01:27:45,612
No, no. I can't leave you.

1303
01:27:45,772 --> 01:27:48,132
I promised I'd put your photo up.

1304
01:27:48,212 --> 01:27:50,252
I promised you'd see Coco.

1305
01:27:50,412 --> 01:27:52,492
We're both out of time, <i>mijo.</i>

1306
01:27:53,812 --> 01:27:57,092
Oh no! No! She can't forget you!

1307
01:27:57,172 --> 01:28:01,012
I just wanted her to know
that I loved her.

1308
01:28:02,332 --> 01:28:03,332
Héctor!

1309
01:28:03,452 --> 01:28:05,412
You have our blessing, Miguel.

1310
01:28:06,092 --> 01:28:07,972
No conditions.

1311
01:28:08,492 --> 01:28:11,252
No! <i>Papá</i> Héctor, please!

1312
01:28:15,452 --> 01:28:16,532
No!

1313
01:28:17,852 --> 01:28:19,012
Go home.

1314
01:28:19,092 --> 01:28:21,932
I promise I won't let
Coco forget you!

1315
01:28:49,252 --> 01:28:50,572
There he is!

1316
01:28:51,852 --> 01:28:53,212
Miguel! Stop!

1317
01:28:58,892 --> 01:29:00,252
Where have you been?

1318
01:29:00,532 --> 01:29:01,812
I need to see <i>Mamá</i> Coco, please.

1319
01:29:02,172 --> 01:29:04,612
What are you doing with that--
Give it to me!

1320
01:29:05,252 --> 01:29:08,972
Miguel, stop! Miguel! Miguel!

1321
01:29:10,932 --> 01:29:14,692
<i>Mamá</i> Coco? Can you hear me?
It's Miguel.

1322
01:29:15,372 --> 01:29:18,852
I saw your <i>papá.</i> Remember? <i>Papá?</i>

1323
01:29:20,212 --> 01:29:25,692
Please! If you forget him,
he'll be gone. Forever.

1324
01:29:26,572 --> 01:29:27,932
Miguel, open this door!

1325
01:29:28,092 --> 01:29:30,812
Here. This was his guitar, right?

1326
01:29:30,892 --> 01:29:32,092
He used to play it to you?

1327
01:29:35,052 --> 01:29:38,612
See? There he is! <i>Papá!</i>

1328
01:29:39,092 --> 01:29:40,972
Remember? <i>Papá?</i>

1329
01:29:44,652 --> 01:29:45,692
Miguel!

1330
01:29:45,772 --> 01:29:48,452
<i>Mamá</i> Coco, please!
Don't forget him.

1331
01:29:55,172 --> 01:29:57,092
What are you doing to that poor woman?

1332
01:29:57,172 --> 01:29:58,372
It's okay, <i>Mamita.</i> It's okay.

1333
01:29:58,532 --> 01:29:59,772
What's gotten into you?

1334
01:30:06,452 --> 01:30:08,132
I thought I'd lost you, Miguel.

1335
01:30:08,292 --> 01:30:09,692
I'm sorry, <i>Papá.</i>

1336
01:30:09,892 --> 01:30:12,932
We're all together now.
That's what matters.

1337
01:30:13,972 --> 01:30:15,132
Not all of us.

1338
01:30:15,292 --> 01:30:17,452
It's okay, <i>Mamita.</i>

1339
01:30:17,532 --> 01:30:20,452
Miguel, you apologize
to your <i>Mamá</i> Coco.

1340
01:30:22,692 --> 01:30:25,492
<i>Mamá</i> Coco?

1341
01:30:30,172 --> 01:30:31,772
Well? Apologize!

1342
01:30:36,092 --> 01:30:38,372
<i>Mamá</i> Coco?

1343
01:30:38,452 --> 01:30:41,892
Your <i>papá,</i> he wanted you to have this.

1344
01:30:43,852 --> 01:30:45,612
<i>Mamá,</i> wait!

1345
01:30:45,772 --> 01:30:49,612
<i>♪ Remember me</i>

1346
01:30:50,972 --> 01:30:53,732
<i>♪ Though I have to say goodbye</i>

1347
01:30:53,932 --> 01:30:56,532
<i>♪ Remember me</i>

1348
01:30:57,212 --> 01:30:59,852
<i>♪ Don't let it make you cry</i>

1349
01:31:00,012 --> 01:31:03,572
<i>♪ For even if I'm far away</i>

1350
01:31:03,732 --> 01:31:09,572
<i>♪ I hold you in my heart</i>
<i>I sing a secret song to you</i>

1351
01:31:09,732 --> 01:31:12,932
<i>♪ Each night we are apart</i>

1352
01:31:13,612 --> 01:31:16,932
<i>♪ Remember me</i>

1353
01:31:17,612 --> 01:31:20,852
<i>♪ Though I have to travel far</i>

1354
01:31:21,532 --> 01:31:23,652
<i>♪ Remember me</i>

1355
01:31:24,332 --> 01:31:27,972
<i>♪ Each time you hear a sad guitar</i>

1356
01:31:29,292 --> 01:31:34,692
<i>♪ Know that I'm with you</i>
<i>The only way that I can be</i>

1357
01:31:36,692 --> 01:31:41,012
<i>♪ Until you're in my arms again</i>

1358
01:31:43,012 --> 01:31:49,492
<i>♪ Remember me ♪</i>

1359
01:31:56,292 --> 01:31:59,412
Elena? What's wrong, <i>mija?</i>

1360
01:31:59,852 --> 01:32:04,052
Nothing, <i>Mamá.</i>
Nothing at all.

1361
01:32:05,412 --> 01:32:08,772
My <i>papá</i> used to sing me that song.

1362
01:32:08,932 --> 01:32:11,532
He loved you, <i>Mamá</i> Coco.

1363
01:32:12,212 --> 01:32:15,852
Your <i>papá</i> loved you so much.

1364
01:32:34,452 --> 01:32:37,772
I kept his letters.

1365
01:32:38,452 --> 01:32:42,692
Poems he wrote me. And...

1366
01:33:02,212 --> 01:33:04,812
<i>Papá</i> was a musician.

1367
01:33:05,452 --> 01:33:07,332
When I was a little girl...

1368
01:33:07,812 --> 01:33:13,172
he and <i>Mamá</i> would sing
such beautiful songs.

1369
01:33:26,132 --> 01:33:27,572
And right over here,

1370
01:33:27,652 --> 01:33:30,252
one of Santa Cecilia's
greatest treasures.

1371
01:33:30,332 --> 01:33:34,052
The home of the esteemed
song writer, Héctor Rivera.

1372
01:33:34,612 --> 01:33:36,132
The letters Héctor wrote home

1373
01:33:36,212 --> 01:33:38,252
for his daughter, Coco,
contain the lyrics...

1374
01:33:38,412 --> 01:33:40,252
for all of your favorite songs.

1375
01:33:40,332 --> 01:33:41,932
Not just <i>Remember Me.</i>

1376
01:33:45,932 --> 01:33:48,052
And that man
is your <i>Papá</i> Julio.

1377
01:33:48,212 --> 01:33:51,332
And there's <i>Tía</i> Rosita
and your <i>Tía</i> Victoria.

1378
01:33:51,492 --> 01:33:54,372
And those two are Oscar and Felipe.

1379
01:33:55,052 --> 01:33:57,492
These aren't just old pictures,
they're our family...

1380
01:33:57,652 --> 01:33:59,732
and they're counting on us
to remember them.

1381
01:34:17,572 --> 01:34:22,892
<i>♪ Say that I'm crazy</i>
<i>or call me a fool</i>

1382
01:34:26,292 --> 01:34:28,852
Enjoy your visit, Héctor.

1383
01:34:29,052 --> 01:34:33,652
<i>♪ But last night it seemed</i>
<i>that I dreamed about you</i>

1384
01:34:36,972 --> 01:34:39,852
<i>- Papá!</i>
- Coco!

1385
01:34:40,052 --> 01:34:44,732
<i>♪ When I opened my mouth</i>
<i>what came out was a song</i>

1386
01:34:44,892 --> 01:34:50,612
<i>♪ And you know every word</i>
<i>and we all sang along</i>

1387
01:34:52,772 --> 01:34:57,772
<i>♪ To a melody played</i>
<i>on the strings of our souls</i>

1388
01:34:58,052 --> 01:35:02,772
<i>♪ And a rhythm that rattled us</i>
<i>down to the bone</i>

1389
01:35:02,972 --> 01:35:07,772
<i>♪ Our love for each other</i>
<i>will live on forever</i>

1390
01:35:09,252 --> 01:35:14,252
<i>♪ In every beat of my proud corazón</i>

1391
01:35:14,412 --> 01:35:18,932
<i>♪ Our love for each other</i>
<i>will live on forever</i>

1392
01:35:20,252 --> 01:35:24,852
<i>♪ In every beat of my proud corazón</i>

1393
01:35:28,532 --> 01:35:32,572
<i>♪ Ay mi familia</i>
<i>Oiga mi gente</i>

1394
01:35:32,732 --> 01:35:36,572
<i>♪ Canten a coro</i>
<i>Let it be known</i>

1395
01:35:36,732 --> 01:35:40,412
<i>♪ Our love for each other</i>
<i>will live on forever</i>

1396
01:35:40,572 --> 01:35:44,572
<i>♪ In every beat of my proud corazón</i>

1397
01:35:45,212 --> 01:35:49,052
<i>♪ Ay mi familia</i>
<i>Oiga mi gente</i>

1398
01:35:49,372 --> 01:35:53,012
<i>♪ Canten a coro</i>
<i>Let it be known</i>

1399
01:35:53,172 --> 01:35:56,972
<i>♪ Our love for each other</i>
<i>will live on forever</i>

1400
01:35:57,132 --> 01:36:01,612
<i>♪ In every beat of my proud corazón ♪</i>

1401
01:36:10,852 --> 01:36:12,252
<i>♪ Remember me</i>

1402
01:36:13,532 --> 01:36:17,972
<i>♪ Though I have to say goodbye</i>
<i>Remember me</i>

